# Subagent Prompts for Zap It Website

## How to Run Subagents

In Cursor Agent mode, use the Task tool with these prompts. Launch multiple in parallel for maximum speed.

Example usage:
```
Task tool → subagent_type: "generalPurpose"
prompt: [paste the prompt below]
```

---

## 1. SEO Audit Subagent

```
You are an SEO auditor for the Zap It Pest Control Melbourne website at /Users/muhammadsharjeel/Documents/Zap/zapit-website/

AUDIT CHECKLIST:
1. Read src/app/layout.tsx — verify metadata title template is "%s | Zap It Pest & Termite Control Melbourne"
2. Read src/app/page.tsx — verify H1 exists, meta description uses SITE_CONFIG.phone
3. Read src/lib/schema.ts — verify JSON-LD: WebSite, Organization, LocalBusiness, Product, FAQ schemas
4. Read src/lib/constants.ts — verify phone is "03 9126 0555", NO old numbers (1800 808 149, 0432 040 404)
5. Read next.config.ts — verify all 301 redirects exist
6. Read src/app/sitemap.ts — verify dynamic sitemap generation
7. Read src/app/robots.ts — verify robots.txt configuration
8. Check ALL page.tsx files for generateMetadata exports
9. Verify NO contact form exists anywhere in the codebase
10. Verify suburb URLs use clean format (/coburg not /pest-control-coburg)

REPORT FORMAT:
- PASS/FAIL for each check
- List any missing items
- Suggest fixes with exact file paths
```

## 2. Code Quality Subagent

```
You are a code quality auditor for the Zap It Pest Control Melbourne website at /Users/muhammadsharjeel/Documents/Zap/zapit-website/

AUDIT CHECKLIST:
1. Run: npx tsc --noEmit (must pass with zero errors)
2. Run: npm run lint (must pass)
3. Check all components use SITE_CONFIG constants — NO hardcoded phone/email/address
4. Check all images use next/image with width/height/alt
5. Check no "any" types exist in TypeScript files
6. Check all client components have 'use client' directive
7. Check no console.log statements in production code
8. Check all links use next/link, not <a> tags for internal links
9. Verify proper error boundaries exist
10. Check accessibility: all buttons have aria-labels, all images have alt text

REPORT: Pass/fail each check with file:line references.
```

## 3. Security Audit Subagent

```
You are a security auditor for the Zap It Pest Control Melbourne website at /Users/muhammadsharjeel/Documents/Zap/zapit-website/

AUDIT CHECKLIST:
1. Read next.config.ts — verify security headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy)
2. Check .env.local.example exists and .env*.local is in .gitignore
3. Verify NO API keys or secrets in any source file
4. Check dangerouslySetInnerHTML is ONLY used in JsonLd.tsx component
5. Verify Supabase client uses NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for browser vars only
6. Check NO server-side secrets exposed to client components
7. Verify forms (if any) have CSRF protection
8. Check external links use rel="noopener noreferrer"
9. Verify images have proper Content-Security-Policy considerations
10. Confirm NO contact form exists (client requirement)

REPORT: Pass/fail each check with severity level.
```

## 4. Design Fidelity Subagent

```
You are a design fidelity auditor comparing the new site to the WordPress original at https://zapitpestmelbourne.com.au/

AUDIT CHECKLIST:
1. Read src/app/globals.css — verify brand colors: #0DC429 (green), #252525 (dark), #333 (text), #f8f9fa (light)
2. Verify Roboto font is configured in layout.tsx
3. Check header height is 70px (h-[70px])
4. Verify sticky Call Now button exists (green, rounded-full, fixed position)
5. Check top bar matches: stars + review count + phone number
6. Verify homepage sections order matches WordPress:
   - Hero → Reviews banner → Who Can Benefit → Pest Services → Industry Solutions
   - Melbourne Coverage + Stats → CBD Specialists → Pest Strategy → Licensed/DHHS
   - Certifications → FAQs → Pricing Calculator
7. Check footer: 4 columns (Company, Operating Hours, Useful Links, Contact)
8. Verify all images from WordPress are downloaded to public/images/
9. Check pricing calculator has all 18 treatments with correct prices
10. Verify FAQ accordion has all 7 questions matching WordPress

REPORT: Section-by-section comparison with MATCH/MISMATCH status.
```

## 5. Performance Subagent

```
You are a performance auditor for the Zap It Pest Control Melbourne website at /Users/muhammadsharjeel/Documents/Zap/zapit-website/

AUDIT CHECKLIST:
1. Run: npm run build — check bundle sizes, verify no warnings
2. Check images use WebP format and next/image optimization
3. Verify fonts use next/font with display: 'swap'
4. Check client components are minimal ('use client' only where needed)
5. Verify static pages use ISR or full static generation where possible
6. Check no unnecessary dependencies in package.json
7. Verify lazy loading for below-fold images
8. Check GTM script uses strategy="afterInteractive"
9. Verify CSS uses Tailwind (no custom CSS bloat)
10. Check no blocking resources in <head>

REPORT: Performance score estimate and optimization suggestions.
```

## Running All Subagents in Parallel

To run a full QA sweep, launch all 5 subagents simultaneously:

```
[In a single message, create 5 Task tool calls with subagent_type: "generalPurpose"]
```

This gives you a comprehensive report in ~30 seconds covering SEO, code quality, security, design fidelity, and performance.
